text:
You can smell the ground floor toilets the moment you enter the main entry atrium. Disgusting!
10/5/25 update: toilet smell everywhere. still disgusting.

Kindly do something about the gatherings outside the Indian international school. Blocking the entrance of the side gate (near Safra). The crowd was worse before this photo was taken. Thought I was Farrer park or Jalan besar area for a moment.

Great tenants but really really hot and humid without fan, aircon or some form of ventilation to cool the place down. Overpriced parking rates as well. Recommend going for a class and leaving the place. No other reason to come here.
Used to be an ITE building now being converted to some commercial building with enrichments and entertainment classes

I see huge potential for interesting development, because it has humongous space. Yoha should attract more F&B operators coming to this compound to make this lively and brighten up the vibe. After 8pm, it feels like ghost town.
